Принцип максимума правдоподобия (напоминание)¶

$X \times Y$ , (.. $w$) .

$P(A|B) = \frac{P(B|A)P(A)}{P(B)}$

$A \equiv w$, $B \equiv Y, X$

$P(w|Y, X) = \frac{P(Y, X|w)P(w)}{P(Y, X)} = \frac{P(Y | X, w)P(X|w)P(w)}{P(Y | X)P(X)} \\ P(w|Y, X) = \frac{P(Y|w, X)P(w)}{P(Y | X)}$

$P(w|Y, X)$

$P(w)$

$P(Y|X, w)$

$\arg\max\limits_w P(w|X, Y) = \arg\max\limits_w {P(Y|w, X)P(w)} \color{red}{=} \arg\max\limits_w \prod\limits_{i=1}^\ell {P(y_i|w, x_i)P(w)} = \\ \arg\max\limits_w \sum\limits_{i=1}^l \log P(y_i|w, x_i) + \log P(w)$

Связь правдоподобия и аппроксимации эмпирического риска (напоминание)¶

  • (maximum likelihood)

$L(w) = \sum\limits_{i=1}^\ell \color{red}{\log P(y_i|w, x_i)} \to \max\limits_w$

$Q(w) = \sum\limits_{i=1}^\ell \color{red}{\mathcal{L}(y_i, x_i, w)} \to \min\limits_w$

  • ,

$ -\log P(y_i|w, x_i) = \mathcal{L}(y_i, x_i, w)$

$P(y|x,w) \equiv $ $g(x,w)$ $\mathcal{L}(M)$

Вероятностный смысл регуляризации¶

$P(y|x, w)$

$P(w; \gamma)$ , $\gamma$ ;

$P(X^\ell, w) = P(X^\ell | w)P(w;\gamma)$

  • (Maximum a Posteriori Probability):

$ L(w) = \log P(X^\ell, w) = \sum\limits_{i=1}^\ell \log P(y_i|w, x_i) + \underbrace{\color{red}{\log P(w; \gamma)}}_{\text{}} \to \max\limits_w $

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib import cm, ticker
from matplotlib.ticker import LinearLocator
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import axes3d, Axes3D

import numpy as np

fig = plt.figure()
ax = Axes3D(fig)

# Make data
x = np.arange(-2, 2, 0.25)
y = np.arange(-2, 2, 0.25)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
R = np.sqrt(X**2 + Y**2)
Z = R**1.2 / 5

# Plot the surface
surf = ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Z, cmap=cm.coolwarm,
                       linewidth=0, antialiased=False)

# Customize the z axis.
ax.set_zlim(-3.01, 1.01)
ax.zaxis.set_major_locator(LinearLocator(10))
# A StrMethodFormatter is used automatically
ax.zaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.StrMethodFormatter("{x:.02f}"))

# Add a color bar which maps values to colors.
fig.colorbar(surf, shrink=0.5, aspect=5)

plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib import cm, ticker
from matplotlib.ticker import LinearLocator
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import axes3d, Axes3D

import numpy as np

fig = plt.figure()
ax = Axes3D(fig)

# Make data
x = np.arange(-2, 2, 0.25)
y = np.arange(-2, 2, 0.25)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
R = np.sqrt(X**2 + Y**2)
Z = np.log(1e-2 + R**1.2 / 5)

# Plot the surface
surf = ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Z, cmap=cm.coolwarm,
                       linewidth=0, antialiased=False)

# Customize the z axis.

  • :

    $ Gain(p, n) = h\left(\frac{P}{\ell} \right) - \frac{p+n}{\ell} h\left(\frac{p}{p+n} \right) - \frac{\ell-p-n}{\ell} h\left(\frac{P-p}{\ell-p-n} \right) \to \max \\ h(q) = -q log_2 q - (1-q) log_2 (1 - q)\ \text{ } $

  • (Gini imurity):

    $IGini(p, n) = IGain(p, n)$ $h(q) = 4q(1 q)$

  • (Fisher's Exact Test):

    $IStat(p, n) = -\frac{1}{\ell} log_2 \frac{C_P^pC_N^n}{C_{P+N}^{p+n}} \to \max$ $p, n$

  • Cohen, Singer, 1999

    $\sqrt{p} - \sqrt{n} \to \max$

In [12]:
def get_grid(data):
    x_min, x_max = data[:, 0].min() - 1, data[:, 0].max() + 1
    y_min, y_max = data[:, 1].min() - 1, data[:, 1].max() + 1
    return np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, 0.01),
                       np.arange(y_min, y_max, 0.01))

In [13]:
def plot_model(X, y, clf, proba=False, legend=True):
    clf.fit(X, y)
    xx2, xx3 = get_grid(X[:, [2,3]])
    shape = xx2.ravel().shape
    grid_xs = np.c_[np.full(shape, X[:,0].mean()), 
                    np.full(shape, X[:,1].mean()),
                    xx2.ravel(), 
                    xx3.ravel()]
    predicted = clf.predict(grid_xs).reshape(xx2.shape)
    if proba:
        probs = clf.predict_proba(grid_xs)
        confidence = probs.max(axis=1).reshape(xx2.shape)
        mesh = plt.pcolormesh(xx2, xx3, confidence, cmap='autumn')
    else:
        mesh = plt.pcolormesh(xx2, xx3, predicted, cmap='autumn')
    plt.scatter(X[:, 2], X[:, 3], c=y, s=150, cmap='autumn', alpha=0.7, edgecolors="black")
    plt.ylim([xx3.min(),xx3.max()])
    plt.xlim([xx2.min(),xx2.max()])
    plt.xlabel(features[2])
    plt.ylabel(features[3])
    if legend:
        if not proba:
            show_legend()
        else:
            cb = plt.colorbar(mesh)
    return clf

Обучение решающего дерева. Алгоритм ID3¶

$v_0 := TreeGrowing(X^)$

1: TreeGrowing($U \subset X^$) $v$

2: StopCriteria ($U$)

3: $\ \ \ $ $v$, $y_v := \text{Major} (U)$

4: , :

$f_v = \arg\max\limits_{f \in F} Gain(f, U)$

5: $Gain (f_v, U) < G_0$

6: $\ \ \ $ $v$, $y_v := \text{Major}(U)$

7: $v$ $f_v$

Критерий ветвления¶

$P(y_i | U_k)$ $v$ $f$ $U = \bigsqcup_{k \in D_v} U_k$:

$\Phi(U_1, \dots , U_{|D_v|}) = \frac{1}{|U|} \sum\limits_{x_i \in U} \mathcal{L}(P(y_i| U_{f(x_i)})) = \\ = \frac{1}{|U|} \sum\limits_{k \in D_v} \sum\limits_{x_i \in U_k} \mathcal{L}(P(y_i| U_{k})) = \sum\limits_{k \in D_v} \frac{|U_k|}{|U|} \Phi(U_k) $

$v$:

$\text{Gain} (f, U) = \Phi(U) - \Phi(U_1, \dots , U_{|D_v|}) = \Phi(U) - \sum\limits_{k \in D_v} \frac{|U_k|}{|U|} \Phi(U_k) \to \max\limits_{f \in F}$
